FARLEY, State Com’r of Excise, v. VOLCKENING. (No. 332-215.) (Supreme Court, Appellate Division, Second Department. November 19, 1915.) Appeal from Special Term, Kings County. Petition of William W. Farley, as State Commissioner of Excise, for an injunction order, etc., against Frederick C. Volckening. Judgment for defendant, and petitioner appeals. Reversed, and motion for injunction granted.

Argued before JENKS, P. J., and STAPLETON, MILLS, RICH, and PUTNAM, JJ.

PER CURIAM.

Order reversed, with $10 costs and disbursements, and motion for injunction granted, with $10 costs, on authority of Farley v. Reinhart, 155 N. Y. Supp. 869, decided November 12, 1915.
